      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn52.13:1.1",
          "pli": "“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāmi dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre santike cā”ti. ",
          "en": "“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that, with clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, I hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.13:1.2",
          "pli": "Tatiyaṃ. ",
